[22:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is basically how many steps you want the AI to go through before outputting your final image. In general, the more steps you have, the higher quality your image would be. But of course, it\'s going to take longer to run. And at a certain'

[22:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'point, if you run it for too many steps, you\'re going to get diminishing returns, and by that point, you\'re just going to be wasting compute. Conversely, if you set the step count to too low of a number, then it\'s going to run faster, but at the sacrifice of some quality.'

